PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1776767959
OL,3,CNew bowel cancer treatment 'highly
OL,4,Ceffective', research suggests
OL,6,FNow, 33 months later, none of the
OL,7,Fpatients have seen a return of their
OL,8,Fcancer ` including those who had no
OL,9,Fsigns of cancer after treatment and
OL,10,Fthose who still had small amounts
OL,11,Fremaining. Of those with remaining
OL,12,Fcancer, it did not grow or spread
OL,13,Fduring follow-up.
OL,15,FNormally, around a quarter of people
OL,16,Fwho have standard surgery and post-op
OL,17,Fchemotherapy see cancer come back
OL,18,Fafter three years, but the new study
OL,19,Fsuggests a short course of
OL,20,Fimmunotherapy before surgery is far
OL,21,Fmore effective.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
