OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1776767959
OL,3,CNew bowel cancer treatment 'highly
OL,4,Ceffective', research suggests
OL,6,FUCLH patient Christopher Burston was
OL,7,Fdiagnosed with bowel cancer in
OL,8,FFebruary 2023 after taking part in
OL,9,Froutine screening. The 73-year-old
OL,10,Freceived three doses of immunotherapy
OL,11,Fover nine weeks, followed by surgery.
OL,13,F"The outcome of the surgery was
OL,14,Fessentially that the cancer had melted
OL,15,Faway ` these were the doctor's words.
OL,16,FThe immunotherapy had had an almost
OL,17,Fimmediate effect," he said.
OL,19,FOver three years later, he remains
OL,20,Fcancer-free.
OL,26,@uD@AOUyD@RO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
